attributes.restaurant_description: Cafe Boheme is a place to eat and drink in laid-back bonhomie, inspired by the 19th century French poets who used to meet on Old Compton Street.
attributes.special_notes:
Cafe Boheme offers reservations for breakfast, lunch and dinner for parties as large as 6 people
To book a larger table please contact the team on 020 7734 0623 
Your booking will allow you 1 hour 45 minutes at the table
Saturday & Sunday Brunch from 12pm until 5pm
Laptops cannot be used
Seating is a mixture of dining tables and counter seating
Reservations are for dining only
Persons under the age of 18 years can accompany you until 9.30pm each day
If you are late to a reservation the table will be held for 15 minutes
Card payments only. Cash not accepted

Reservations are for dining only. 

Parties of 1-2 people will receive 1.5 hours at the table.

attributes.restaurant_description: Meat and fish cooked over cherry and apple wood embers, and House regulars from around the world.
attributes.special_notes:
This is the indoor dining space of DUMBO House.

There is a two-hour dining limit on all tables.

Starting Friday, September 10, all members over the age of 12 must present a record of at least one dose of the Coronavirus vaccination upon arrival at our Houses in New York.  Guests must present a record of at least one dose of the Coronavirus vaccination as well as an acceptable form of identification.

•	Examples of documentation include a physical vaccination card, a photo of vaccination card, domestic or international passes – e.g., Excelsior or NHS pass, and commercial solutions like Clear
•	Please let us know if you are exempt due to disability and will need accommodations
•	You can request for your vaccine status to be added to your member profile, so that you don’t need to provide proof on subsequent visits

attributes.restaurant_description: Cecconi’s Dumbo is a modern day classic Italian restaurant near Brooklyn Bridge park, specializing in hand-made pasta, wood-fired pizza and other Italian staples. Originating in Venice and with outposts in London and West Hollywood, Cecconi’s has become a critically acclaimed dining destination featuring simply prepared Venetian inspired food.
attributes.special_notes:
All guests must wear a mask when not seated, eating or drinking due to current COVID-19 guidelines.

Starting Friday, September 10, all members over the age of 12 must present a record of at least one dose of the Coronavirus vaccination upon arrival at our Houses in New York.  Guests must present a record of at least one dose of the Coronavirus vaccination as well as an acceptable form of identification.

•	Examples of documentation include a physical vaccination card, a photo of vaccination card, domestic or international passes – e.g., Excelsior or NHS pass, and commercial solutions like Clear
•	Please let us know if you are exempt due to disability and will need accommodations
•	You can request for your vaccine status to be added to your member profile, so that you don’t need to provide proof on subsequent visits
